# AMR-GigaWord 200k

# ::id 0 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok a traffic peak starts in china as the spring festival holidays end and millions of people are heading back to work .
# ::alignments
(s / start-01
      :ARG1 (p / peak-01
            :ARG1 (t / traffic))
      :location (c / country
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "China"))
      :time (a / and
            :op1 (e / end-01
                  :ARG1 (h / holiday
                        :mod (f / festival
                              :time (d / date-entity
                                    :season (s2 / spring)))))
            :op2 (h2 / head-02
                  :ARG0 (p2 / person
                        :quant (m / multiple
                              :op1 1000000))
                  :ARG1 (w / work-01
                        :ARG0 p2)
                  :direction (b / back))))

# ::id 1 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok president luiz inacio lula da silva appointed two lawmakers to key cabinet positions tuesday , part of a long-awaited reform aimed at shoring up support for his governing coalition .
# ::alignments
(a / appoint-01
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Luiz"
                  :op2 "Inacio"
                  :op3 "Lula"
                  :op4 "da"
                  :op5 "Silva")
            :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                  :ARG2 (p2 / president)))
      :ARG1 (p3 / person
            :quant 2
            :ARG0-of (h2 / have-org-role-91
                  :ARG2 (l / legislate-01)))
      :ARG2 (p4 / position
            :ARG2-of (k / key-02)
            :ARG1-of (h3 / have-org-role-91
                  :ARG2 (c / cabinet)))
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (t / tuesday))
      :part-of (r / reform-01
            :ARG1-of (a2 / aim-02
                  :ARG2 (s / shore-up-01
                        :ARG1 (s2 / support-01
                              :ARG1 (c2 / coalition
                                    :ARG0-of (g / govern-01)
                                    :poss p))))
            :ARG1-of (w / wait-01
                  :ARG1-of (l2 / long-03))))

# ::id 2 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

                  :op1 "David"
                  :op2 "Zabriskie")
            :mod (c / country
                  :name (n2 / name
                        :op1 "America")))
      :ARG1 (t / tour
            :name (n3 / name
                  :op1 "Missouri"))
      :manner (f / finish-07
            :ARG0 p
            :ARG1 (p2 / pack
                  :mod (m / main)
                  :part-of (s / stage
                        :mod (f2 / final)))
            :path (s2 / street
                  :location (c2 / city
                        :name (n4 / name
                              :op1 "Kansas")
                        :location (d / downtown)))))

# ::id 3 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

                  :quant 8
                  :mod (e / ethnic-group
                        :name (n / name
                              :op1 "Kurd"))

                        :ARG2 (s / separatism
                              :ARG2-of (p2 / punishable-02
                                    :ARG3 (d / die-01)
                                    :mod (t2 / theory))))

                        :ARG1 (g / government-organization
                              :name (n2 / name
                                    :op1 "Turkish"
                                    :op2 "Parliament"))
                        :ARG2 (m / member)))

                  :weekday (t3 / thursday))))

# ::id 4 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok a newly conducted geological survey has found more than #,### underground rivers with a total length of ##,### kilometers in southwest china 's rock desert areas .
# ::alignments
(f / find-01
      :ARG0 (s / survey-01
            :mod (g / geology)
            :ARG1-of (c / conduct-01
                  :ARG1-of (n / new-01)))
      :ARG1 (r / river
            :location (u / underground)
            :quant (m / more-than
                  :op1 (d / distance-quantity
                        :quant 1
                        :unit (k / kilometer)
                        :ARG2-of (t / total-01))))
      :location (a / area
            :mod (d2 / desert
                  :mod (r2 / rock))
            :location (s2 / southwest
                  :part-of (c2 / country
                        :name (n2 / name
                              :op1 "China")))))

                        :ARG2 (p4 / peace))

                        :mod (n4 / next))))
      :time (d2 / date-entity
            :weekday (t / tuesday))
      :time (a / after
            :op1 (m2 / meet-03
                  :ARG0 p

                        :name (n5 / name
                              :op1 "Hosni"
                              :op2 "Mubarak")

                              :ARG2 (p6 / president))))))

# ::id 6 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

                  :ARG1 (s / state
                        :name (n / name
                              :op1 "Mississippi"))
                  :ARG2 (g / governor
                        :mod (p2 / political-party
                              :name (n2 / name
                                    :op1 "Republican")))))
      :ARG1 (s2 / stall-01
            :ARG0 (f / fail-01
                  :ARG1 (g2 / government-organization
                        :ARG0-of (g3 / govern-01))
                  :ARG2 (a / approve-01
                        :ARG0 g2
                        :ARG1 (f2 / fund-01
                              :ARG1 (a2 / and
                                    :op1 (r / road)
                                    :op2 (s3 / school)
                                    :op3 (c / construct-01
                                          :ARG1 (h2 / house-01)))
                              :mod (e / emergency))))
            :ARG1 (e2 / effort-01
                  :ARG0 s
                  :ARG1 (r2 / rebuild-01
                        :ARG0 s))
            :time (a3 / after
                  :op1 (n3 / natural-disaster
                        :name (n4 / name
                              :op1 "Katrina"))))
      :time (w / wednesday))

      :time (w / wednesday))

                                                :ARG1 c))

                                                :name (n2 / name
                                                      :op1 "Iraq")))
                                    :ARG1-of (l / legal-02
                                          :polarity -)))))
            :ARG1 (o / office
                  :poss (f / firm
                        :mod (c4 / country
                              :name (n3 / name
                                    :op1 "Germany"))))
            :time (w / week
                  :mod (l2 / last)
                  :ARG1-of (ii3 / include-91
                        :ARG2 (p3 / probe-01
                              :ARG1 (b / breach-01
                                    :ARG1 (e3 / embargo-01

                        :mod (c3 / champion
                              :mod g

                                    :op1 "World"
                                    :op2 "Cup"))))))
